# =============================================================================
# AxTask — Render Web Service environment template (no secrets; safe to commit)
# =============================================================================
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Generate scaffold + secrets + paste guide:
#        npm run render:env-bootstrap -- --domain=your-domain.com [--invite]
#      Or copy: cp .env.render.example .env.render   (PowerShell: Copy-Item)
#   2. Fill remaining keys from dashboards (script prints a checklist) — never commit .env.render.
#   3. Enter the same keys/values in Render → Web Service → Manage → Environment.
#      Health Check Path /ready is under Events → Settings (not Environment). See docs/RENDER_WEB_SERVICE_PASTE_CHECKLIST.md
#
# Or use Infrastructure as Code: see render.yaml in the repo root (sync: false
# vars must still be set in the Render dashboard or via `render secret`).
#
# Build: npm ci && npm run build     Start: npm run start     Health check: /ready
# =============================================================================

NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
FORCE_HTTPS=true

# Primary public hostname (host checks / redirects)
CANONICAL_HOST=your-domain.com

# Public origin of the app (OAuth redirects, links)
BASE_URL=https://your-domain.com

# Neon (or other) Postgres — use Render’s “sync” or paste from Neon dashboard
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require

# ≥32 random chars; unique per environment
SESSION_SECRET=replace-with-long-random-secret

# Optional: Replit hostname if you still use fallback routing
# REPLIT_FALLBACK_HOST=

# --- Auth (set only what you use) ---
# AUTH_PROVIDER=local | google | workos | replit
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Google OAuth authorized redirect: https://your-domain.com/api/auth/google/callback
#
# WORKOS_API_KEY=
# WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=
# WORKOS_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-domain.com/api/auth/workos/callback
#
# REPL_ID=
# ISSUER_URL=https://replit.com/oidc

# Production defaults to invite mode if unset — set explicitly:
# REGISTRATION_MODE=invite
# INVITE_CODE=your-single-use-or-shared-invite

# --- Email / MFA (required for production admin step-up email OTP) ---
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# RESEND_FROM=noreply@your-domain.com
#
# SMS MFA (optional):
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# TWILIO_MESSAGING_SERVICE_SID=
# TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=

# --- Build-time (set on Render if you use these features) ---
# Browser push (Vite inlines at build — set before deploy if using push):
# VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
#
# Shown on /contact as a mailto: for human support (optional):
# VITE_CONTACT_EMAIL=you@yourdomain.com
#
# Bump after breaking API/cache shape changes to reset client persisted queries:
# VITE_QUERY_PERSIST_BUSTER=v1

# --- Optional product / integrations ---
# GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_KEY=
# DONATE_URL=
# NODEWEAVER_URL=
# ATTACHMENT_UPLOAD_SECRET=

# Premium feature flags (default on unless set to "false")
# PREMIUM_FLAG_SAVED_VIEWS=true
# PREMIUM_FLAG_REVIEW_WORKFLOWS=true
# ... (see server/routes.ts PREMIUM_FLAG_*)

# Dev-only sign-in hint — omitted in production by the server
# AXTASK_LOGIN_PRETEXT=
